07/03/2004
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The three independent lawyers who are overseeing the trial of former Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic formally asked the UN court to drop the genocide charge against the defendant in the part of the case involving Bosnia and Herzegovina. Steven Kay, Branislav Tapuskovic and Timothy McCormack also called for some lesser charges to be dropped and dozens of paragraphs in the indictment to be stricken. The court has not set a date for a ruling on the motion. (AP, Reuters, AFP - 05/03/04)
